text: The COVID-19 pandemic in Guinea is part of the worldwide pandemic of coronavirus disease 2019 () caused by severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (). The virus was confirmed to have reached Guinea in March 2020. On 13 March 2020, Guinea's first confirmed COVID-19 case was reported. Confirmed cases doubled from eight to sixteen on 29 March. ==References== Guinea Category:Guinea
